    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6976" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅτε</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">when,
            since.</span>—(1) temporal, w. the same constructions as other
          relative words, see <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄν, κέν</span>. Freq. in
          similes, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὡς δ᾽ ὅτε, ὡς δ̓ ὁτ̓ ἄν</span>, and
          without verb, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὡς ὅτε</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">just
            like;</span> there is nothing peculiar in such a usage.—(2) less
          often causal, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.244</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
